   <refnamediv>
       <refname>bmapost_g </refname>
               <refpurpose>Evaluate log marginal posterior of a BMA model </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>lpost = bmapost_g(y,x,vin,g)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> y </term> =    dependent variable vector</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> x     </term> =    explanatory variables matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> vin </term> =    a 1xk vector of columns to use from x</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> g </term> =    g-prior</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term>  lpost </term> =    log marginal posterior, a scalar containing the log marginal</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Function used for bayesian model averaging codes. It evaluates the log marginal posterior of each new model selected in a MCMC step
 
<para> </para>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Emmanuel Michaux 2006
        </refsection>
</refentry>
